PROCESSING.ExperimentalProcedure: Matrix polymer, cross-linker and catalyst were dissolved in solvent and were mixed at room temperature to make pre-gel solution. Pre-gel solution was then transferred to a glass mold for gelation to take place.

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: Dynamic frequency sweep tests were conducted on SR and FC gels on a strain-controlled oscillatory rheometer (RSAIII, TA Instruments) using a cylinder geometry.

LinearElastic.preCrackingProcess: a 2-mm initial crack was introduced to the middle point of the sample edge by a sharp blade

strainAmplitude.description: Compression with 2.0% strain was loaded in advance
